Classful Subnetting

Although this method of subnetting is now favored by other more relevant forms of subnetting. This is still relevant whenever you hear people talk about what kind of address they are interacting with. This was also a method of describing an ip address as its related to its subnet mask. You can imagine if two people are talking about the objects in their room and theyre talking about certain id cards being class A, it means those default subnet masks(rooms) have 8 bits for the network but 24 for the host. A class B is split evenly with 16 for the network and 16 for the host and last but not least for the class C addresses they have 24 for the network but only 8 for the host.

so it looks like this:

Class A: 255.0.0.0 (network.host.host.host)
Class B: 255.255.0.0 (network.network.host.host)
Class C: 255.255.255.0 (network.network.network.host) 

But yeah this hasn't been used since 1993 for subnet masking purposes, although for learning the basics or in casual conversation you will still hear these terms. And for the critical function being that its used as a starting point when subnetting our networks. its like youre the engineer for the said building we're talking about we all have to start provisioning the room space so this is one way to start the plan drawing process. 

Now you know what kind of default subnet masks are there how is it related onto our id cards or ip addresses? well, a neat way for you to recognize what kind of class an id card belongs to is to look at its first set of bits, so here's a chart to help you out:

Class A Leading bits:0xxx(0-127)
Class B Leading bits:10xx(128-191)
Class C Leading bits:110x(192-223)
Class D(Multicast) Leading bits: 1110(224-239)
Class E(Reserved) Leading bits: 1111(240-255)

Class D ones are assigned to multicast communication and what is that? where its a network transmission method where a single data stream is sent by one or multiple senders to multiple specific senders as well. It's like if the landlord of your said building wanted to tell a lot of people but not everyone something important about their rooms so on one day he goes and puts letters under the doorsteps of you rooms and on other days he asks a bunch of people to do it for him 

Class E ones are reserved by IANA the guys who make all of this ip addressing wizardry possible but for their own researching purposes and are never made public at all
